Tier 4: Substrate complete and ready for SWP
Substrate clean and dry. Free from dirt/debris contamination and ready for membrane
All lumps and sharp concrete bits ground/hammered down
Substrate clean, dry, free of debris
Install VCL over primer sheets lapped minimum 50mm
Surface is dry prior to install
Vapor control layer has been checked and no damage
Install SA primer to top surface of VCL
Install Board bond 600u in specified pattern
SS mesh laid flat over all surfaces
Surface is dry prior to install
Install board bond 600u in specified pattern
Roof board installed in brick pattern where possible
Wipe and clean laps prior to welding
Test weld with the welding machines
Probe of seam with QA hook
Installed correctly according to specifications (right way around)
Fixings and welding done according to specifications and details
Probe of weld with QA hook
All installation work complete, checked and reviewed as per specification

resource: QA - Fibertite Warm Roof Over Metal Deck Checklist

Tier 4: Substrate complete and ready for SWP
Base deck screwed down in every pan
Sheet edges stiched together at 300mm centres
Is the substrate clean, dry and clear of swarf
All areas covered and sheets lapped 50mm
All holes/penetrations patched and water tight
Surface is dry prior to install
Vapour control layer has been checked for no damage
Insulation board installed in a brick pattern
Joints flush (no gaps between boards on ends)
Fixings at correct spacing according to spec if no Securock in system.
Correct length screw with load washer
Installed as per wind uplift fixing plan
Laying of membrane into the adhesive
Wipe and clean of laps prior to welding
Probe of seam with QA hook
Installed correctly according to specifications (Right way around)
Fixings and welding done according to specifications and details
Probe of weld with QA hook
All installation work complete, checked and reviewed as per specification
